Velocity
Definition	A measure of the work that is completed per set amount of time.
Calculated by:	Only taking into account the completed projects.
Purpose	To determine how long something takes to complete, as to use it to estimate other potential projects.
Team Velocity
How often calculated.	It is re-calculated every time a project is completed, as to keep up to date estimates.
Calculated by:	It is calculated by using only completed items and using historical data.
Purpose	This will allow the Scrum Master to make estimates of the completion of any project.


Capacity
Definition	The maximum amount of work that a development team can be completed in a sprint.
Purpose	To allow the leader to determine how much the tea, can do each sprint.

